The paper deals with the development and analysis of a distributed algorithm for cooperative estimation using wireless sensor networks. This involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT) for communication and compression of sensor data, control systems (cs.SY) for the design and analysis of the distributed algorithm, networked systems (cs.NI) for the study of the wireless sensor network, machine learning (cs.MA) for the use of the recursive least-squares algorithm, and machine learning (cs.LG) for the performance analysis of the algorithm.
